author: bdaniel
msg: TUSCANY-3711 Change generated binding and port names to match recommended values from the ws binding spec appendix D. The old value for service name is still being used for the time being.

author: minfrin
msg: Support Cache-Control: no-cache with a header name, and private with a
header name, which causes a cached entry to require revalidation (ie
is always not-fresh), as per RFC2616 14.9.1.

author: minfrin
msg: Don't attempt to kill a stale entry that cannot be revalidated so early
in the process, as this will happen later anyway as necessary. We may want
to serve the stale entry should the backend not be available.

author: minfrin
msg: As cache_control_t is public, make ap_cache_control() public with it. Bump
the MMN for addition of ap_cache_control(), and the addition of cache_control_t
